that I'm more at home here

885
01:05:15.912 --> 01:05:19.248
among the birds and the flowers

886
01:05:19.332 --> 01:05:22.501
and the wind that moves through
the trees like a restless sea, hmm?

887
01:05:22.585 --> 01:05:24.587
How poetic.

888
01:05:24.670 --> 01:05:26.631
Yes, it was rather, wasn't it?

889
01:05:27.715 --> 01:05:30.676
More at home here than in Vienna,

890
01:05:30.760 --> 01:05:33.179
in all your glittering salons,

891
01:05:33.262 --> 01:05:37.767
gossiping gaily with bores I detest,
soaking myself in champagne,

892
01:05:37.850 --> 01:05:41.812
stumbling about to waltzes by Strauss
I can't even remember.

893
01:05:41.896 --> 01:05:44.106
-Is that what you're trying to say?
-More or less, yes.

894
01:05:44.190 --> 01:05:45.942
Now, what ever gave you that idea?

895
01:05:47.735 --> 01:05:51.364
(sighs) Oh, I do like it here, Georg.

896
01:05:51.447 --> 01:05:53.783
It's so lovely and peaceful.

897
01:05:53.866 --> 01:05:56.077
How can you leave it
as often as you do?

898
01:05:56.160 --> 01:05:59.038
Oh, pretending to be
madly active, I suppose.

899
01:05:59.121 --> 01:06:02.625
Activity suggests a life filled
with purpose.

900
01:06:02.708 --> 01:06:05.753
Could it be running away from memories?

901
01:06:06.337 --> 01:06:08.464
Mm-hm.

902
01:06:08.547 --> 01:06:12.843
Or perhaps just searching
for a reason to stay.

903
01:06:12.927 --> 01:06:16.430
Oh, I hope that's why you've been
coming to Vienna so often.

904
01:06:17.431 --> 01:06:19.433
Or were there other distractions there?

905
01:06:19.517 --> 01:06:21.727
Oh, I'd hardly call you
a mere distraction, darling.

906
01:06:21.811 --> 01:06:24.188
Well, what would you
call me, Georg?

907
01:06:24.271 --> 01:06:27.858
Hmm. Lovely.

908
01:06:29.318 --> 01:06:31.821
Charming, witty, graceful.
The perfect hostess.

909
01:06:31.904 --> 01:06:35.074
And, uh... you're gonna
hate me for this...

910
01:06:35.157 --> 01:06:37.618
...in a way, my savior.

911
01:06:37.702 --> 01:06:39.704
Oh, how unromantic.

912
01:06:39.787 --> 01:06:42.498
I would be an ungrateful
wretch if I didn't tell you at least once

913
01:06:42.581 --> 01:06:44.917
that it was you who brought some
meaning back into my life.

914
01:06:47.461 --> 01:06:50.464
Oh, I am amusing, I suppose.

915
01:06:50.548 --> 01:06:53.551
And I do have the finest
couturier in Vienna...

916
01:06:53.634 --> 01:06:55.678
and the most glittering
circle of friends.

917
01:06:55.761 --> 01:06:58.806
-And I do give some rather gay parties.
-(laughs) Oh, yes.

918
01:06:58.889 --> 01:07:02.476
But take all that away,
and you have just...

919
01:07:02.560 --> 01:07:07.523
wealthy, unattached little me
searching just like you.

920
01:07:09.066 --> 01:07:10.693
(chuckles)

921
01:07:13.154 --> 01:07:15.072
More strudel, Herr Detweiler?

922
01:07:15.156 --> 01:07:17.033
-How many have I had?
-Two.

923
01:07:17.116 --> 01:07:19.326
-Make it an uneven three.
-(chuckles)

924
01:07:22.079 --> 01:07:25.791
Still eating, Max, hmm?
Tsk, tsk. Must be unhappy.

925
01:07:25.875 --> 01:07:28.169
That marvelous mixed quartet
I've been trying for months

926
01:07:28.252 --> 01:07:30.629
-to steal away from Sol Hurok--
-What happened, darling?

927
01:07:30.713 --> 01:07:32.715
Yesterday, Sascha Petrie stole them first.

928
01:07:32.798 --> 01:07:34.425
If there's one thing I hate, it's a thief.

929
01:07:34.508 --> 01:07:37.887
Max, you really must try
and learn to, uh, love yourself.

930
01:07:37.970 --> 01:07:40.514
For this, I had to call Paris,
Rome and Stockholm.

931
01:07:40.598 --> 01:07:43.851
-On Georg's telephone, of course?
-How else could I afford it?

932
01:07:44.685 --> 01:07:46.771
Oh, dear, I like rich people.

933
01:07:46.854 --> 01:07:50.024
I like the way they live.
I like the way I live when I'm with them.

934
01:07:50.107 --> 01:07:52.151
I wonder where the children are.

935
01:07:52.234 --> 01:07:54.862
Obviously they must have heard
I was coming and went into hiding.

936
01:07:54.945 --> 01:07:57.907
I was hoping they'd
be here to welcome you.

937
01:07:57.990 --> 01:08:01.660
Uh, Max, do step out of character
for a moment and try and be charming.

938
01:08:06.499 --> 01:08:08.709
(door opens, closes)

939
01:08:11.253 --> 01:08:12.630
Well?

940
01:08:13.380 --> 01:08:15.216
Well what?

941
01:08:15.299 --> 01:08:18.094
Have you made up Georg's mind yet?
Do I hear wedding bells?

942
01:08:18.177 --> 01:08:20.471
-Pealing madly.
-Marvelous.

943
01:08:20.554 --> 01:08:23.265
-But not necessarily for me.
-What kind of talk's that?

944
01:08:23.349 --> 01:08:25.518
That is none-of-your-business talk, Max.

945
01:08:25.601 --> 01:08:27.978
I'm terribly fond of Georg,
and I will not have you toying with us.

946
01:08:28.062 --> 01:08:29.939
But I'm a child. I like toys.

947
01:08:30.022 --> 01:08:32.024
So tell me everything.

948
01:08:32.108 --> 01:08:34.652
Oh, come on, tell Max
every teensy-weensy,

949
01:08:34.735 --> 01:08:37.863
intimate, disgusting detail.

950
01:08:37.947 --> 01:08:42.743
Well, let's just say I have a feeling
I may be here on approval.

951
01:08:42.827 --> 01:08:44.787
Well, I approve of that.
How can you miss?

952
01:08:44.870 --> 01:08:46.330
Far too easily.

953
01:08:46.413 --> 01:08:49.375
If I know you, darling, and I do,
you will find a way.

954
01:08:49.458 --> 01:08:52.461
-Oh, he's no ordinary man.
-No. He's rich.

955
01:08:52.545 --> 01:08:55.131
When his wife died,
she left him with a terrible heartache.

956
01:08:55.214 --> 01:08:58.008
And when your husband died,
he left you with a terrible fortune.

957
01:08:58.092 --> 01:09:00.219
Oh, Max, you really are a beast.

958
01:09:00.302 --> 01:09:02.471
You and Georg are like family to me.

959
01:09:02.555 --> 01:09:04.473
That's why I want to see
you two get married.

960
01:09:04.557 --> 01:09:07.393
We must keep all that
lovely money in the family.

961
01:09:07.476 --> 01:09:09.395
(chuckles)

962
01:09:24.243 --> 01:09:25.911
What are you doing there?

963
01:09:25.995 --> 01:09:29.290
Captain von Trapp!
I was just looking for--

964
01:09:30.833 --> 01:09:33.460
I didn't see--
I mean, I didn't know you were--

965
01:09:33.544 --> 01:09:34.962
Heil Hitler!

966
01:09:36.547 --> 01:09:37.965
Who are you?

967
01:09:38.048 --> 01:09:40.050
I have a telegram for Herr Detweiler.

968
01:09:40.885 --> 01:09:42.344
I'm Herr Detweiler.

969
01:09:42.428 --> 01:09:43.429
Yes, sir.

970
01:09:48.559 --> 01:09:50.853
All right, you've delivered your telegram.
Now get out.

971
01:09:57.902 --> 01:10:00.154
Oh, Georg, he's just a boy.

972
01:10:00.237 --> 01:10:01.697
Yes, and I'm just an Austrian.

973
01:10:01.780 --> 01:10:04.491
What's gonna happen's going to happen.
Just make sure it doesn't happen to you.

974
01:10:04.575 --> 01:10:07.369
Max, don't you ever say that again!

975
01:10:07.453 --> 01:10:11.123
You know I have no political convictions.
Can I help it if other people do?

976
01:10:11.207 --> 01:10:12.625
Oh, yes, you can help it!

977
01:10:14.210 --> 01:10:15.461
You must help it.

978
01:10:26.639 --> 01:10:28.224
Hello.

979
01:10:30.559 --> 01:10:33.479
You're far away.
Where are you?

980
01:10:33.562 --> 01:10:37.316
In a world that's disappearing,
I'm afraid.

981
01:10:38.525 --> 01:10:40.945
Is there any way I could bring you back
to the world I'm in?

982
01:10:41.028 --> 01:10:42.446
(children chattering)

983
01:10:42.529 --> 01:10:44.907
(chattering, screaming)

984
01:10:44.990 --> 01:10:49.536
CHILDREN:<i> ♪ Sew, a needle</i>
<i>pulling thread ♪</i>

985
01:10:49.620 --> 01:10:53.999
<i>♪ La, a note to follow sew ♪</i>

986
01:10:54.083 --> 01:10:57.753
<i>♪ Tea, a drink with jam and bread ♪</i>

987
01:10:57.836 --> 01:11:01.674
<i>♪ That will bring us back to Do ♪</i>

988
01:11:01.757 --> 01:11:04.426
<i>-♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Doe, a deer ♪</i>

989
01:11:04.510 --> 01:11:07.429
<i>-♪ A female deer ♪</i>
-(screaming, laughing)

990
01:11:07.513 --> 01:11:10.766
-CHILDREN: Father! Father!
-What? Is it your father?

991
01:11:10.849 --> 01:11:14.853
Oh! Oh, Captain.
You're home. Oh! Oh!

992
01:11:14.937 --> 01:11:17.523
(screaming)

993
01:11:22.027 --> 01:11:24.238
Come out of that water at once!

994
01:11:33.914 --> 01:11:36.458
Oh! You must be Baroness Schraeder.

995
01:11:36.542 --> 01:11:39.378
(stifles laughter)

996
01:11:41.672 --> 01:11:43.924
Oh, I'm soaked to the skin!

997
01:11:45.092 --> 01:11:48.971
(children speaking at once)

998
01:11:49.054 --> 01:11:51.598
(whistle blows)

999
01:11:56.687 --> 01:11:58.188
Straight line!

1000
01:12:12.411 --> 01:12:14.330
This is Baroness Schraeder.

1001
01:12:17.583 --> 01:12:21.211
And these are my children.

1002
01:12:22.171 --> 01:12:23.464
How do you do?

1003
01:12:24.923 --> 01:12:26.550
All right. Go inside.
Dry off. Clean up.

1004
01:12:26.633 --> 01:12:28.510
Change your clothes.
Report back here.

1005
01:12:28.594 --> 01:12:29.887
Immediately!

1006
01:12:34.683 --> 01:12:36.518
Fräulein, you will stay here, please.

1007
01:12:38.645 --> 01:12:40.064
I, uh-- (clears throat)

1008
01:12:40.147 --> 01:12:42.358
I think I'd better go see
what Max is up to.

1009
01:12:52.201 --> 01:12:53.702
Now, fräulein...

1010
01:12:55.704 --> 01:12:57.498
I want a truthful answer from you.

1011
01:12:58.248 --> 01:13:00.292
Yes, Captain?

1012
01:13:00.376 --> 01:13:03.504
Is it possible--
or could I have just imagined it--

1013
01:13:05.798 --> 01:13:10.469
Have my children, by any chance,
been climbing trees today?

1014
01:13:10.552 --> 01:13:13.806
-Yes, Captain.
-I see.

1015
01:13:14.848 --> 01:13:19.603
And where, may I ask,
did they get these, um...

1016
01:13:19.686 --> 01:13:21.647
-Play clothes.
-Oh, is that what you call them?

1017
01:13:21.730 --> 01:13:24.566
I made them from the drapes
that used to hang in my bedroom.

1018
01:13:26.068 --> 01:13:28.237
-Drapes?
-They still had plenty of wear left.

1019
01:13:28.320 --> 01:13:29.822
The children have been everywhere in them.

1020
01:13:30.697 --> 01:13:35.285
Do you mean to tell me that my children
have been roaming about Salzburg

1021
01:13:35.369 --> 01:13:37.996
dressed up in nothing but some old drapes?

1022
01:13:38.080 --> 01:13:40.749
Mm-hm, and having a marvelous time.

1023
01:13:40.833 --> 01:13:42.918
-They have uniforms.
-Straitjackets, if you'll forgive me.

1024
01:13:43.001 --> 01:13:44.503
I will not forgive you for that.

1025
01:13:44.586 --> 01:13:46.255
Children cannot do the things
they're supposed to do

1026
01:13:46.338 --> 01:13:48.048
if they have to worry about
spoiling their precious clothes.

1027
01:13:48.132 --> 01:13:49.675
-I haven't heard them complain yet.
-Well, they wouldn't dare.

1028
01:13:49.758 --> 01:13:51.593
They love you too much.
They fear you too much.

1029
01:13:51.677 --> 01:13:53.387
I don't wish you to discuss
my children in this manner.

1030
01:13:53.470 --> 01:13:55.514
You've got to hear from someone.
You're never home long enough--

1031
01:13:55.597 --> 01:13:57.224
I said I don't want
to hear any more from you--

1032
01:13:57.307 --> 01:13:59.101
I know you don't, but you've got to!

1033
01:14:00.436 --> 01:14:02.938
-Now, take Liesl--
-You'll not say one word about Liesl.

1034
01:14:03.021 --> 01:14:04.982
One of these days, you're gonna
wake up and find she's a woman.

1035
01:14:05.065 --> 01:14:07.359
You won't even know her.
And Friedrich, he's a boy,

1036
01:14:07.443 --> 01:14:09.486
but wants to be a man like you,
and there's no one to show him how.

1037
01:14:09.570 --> 01:14:10.988
Don't you dare tell me about my son.

1038
01:14:11.071 --> 01:14:13.282
Brigitta could tell you about him,
if you'd let her get close to you.

1039
01:14:13.365 --> 01:14:15.492
She notices everything.
And Kurt pretends he's tough

1040
01:14:15.576 --> 01:14:17.161
not to show how hurt he is

1041
01:14:17.244 --> 01:14:18.495
-when you brush him aside...
-That will do.

1042
01:14:18.579 --> 01:14:20.414
...the way you do all of them.
Louisa, I don't know about,

1043
01:14:20.497 --> 01:14:22.332
-but someone has to find out about her.
-I said that will do!

1044
01:14:22.416 --> 01:14:25.961
And the little ones just want to be loved.
Oh, please, love them, love them all.

1045
01:14:26.044 --> 01:14:28.005
I don't care to hear anything further
from you about my children!

1046
01:14:28.088 --> 01:14:30.966
-I am not finished yet, Captain!
-Oh, yes, you are, Captain--

1047
01:14:33.093 --> 01:14:34.636
Fräulein.

1048
01:14:35.554 --> 01:14:39.850
Now, you will pack
your things this minute

1049
01:14:39.933 --> 01:14:41.810
and return to the abbey.

1050
01:14:41.894 --> 01:14:43.520
CHILDREN:<i> ♪ The hills are alive ♪</i>

1051
01:14:43.604 --> 01:14:46.732
<i>-♪ With the sound of music ♪</i>
-What's that?

1052
01:14:46.815 --> 01:14:49.401
-LIESL:<i> ♪Ah ah ah ah ♪</i>
-It's singing.

1053
01:14:49.485 --> 01:14:52.863
Yes, I realize it's singing,
but who is singing?

1054
01:14:52.946 --> 01:14:54.698
The children.

1055
01:14:54.781 --> 01:14:58.076
<i>-♪ For a thousand years ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Ah ah ah ah ♪</i>

1056
01:14:58.160 --> 01:14:59.620
The children?

1057
01:14:59.703 --> 01:15:02.498
I taught them something
to sing for the baroness.

1058
01:15:02.581 --> 01:15:05.584
<i>♪ With the sound of music ♪</i>

1059
01:15:05.667 --> 01:15:08.003
<i>♪ Ah ah ah ah ♪</i>

1060
01:15:08.086 --> 01:15:10.839
<i>♪ My heart wants to sing ♪</i>

1061
01:15:10.923 --> 01:15:14.551
<i>♪ Every song it hears ♪</i>

1062
01:15:14.635 --> 01:15:17.554
<i>♪ Every song that it hears ♪</i>

1063
01:15:17.638 --> 01:15:19.848
<i>♪ My heart wants to beat ♪</i>

1064
01:15:19.932 --> 01:15:23.310
<i>♪ Like the wings</i>
<i>of the birds that rise ♪</i>

1065
01:15:23.393 --> 01:15:26.021
<i>♪ From the lake to the trees ♪</i>

1066
01:15:26.104 --> 01:15:27.856
<i>♪ To the trees ♪</i>

1067
01:15:27.940 --> 01:15:33.612
<i>♪ My heart wants to sigh</i>
<i>like a chime that flies ♪</i>

1068
01:15:33.695 --> 01:15:37.491
<i>♪ From a church on a breeze ♪</i>

1069
01:15:37.574 --> 01:15:40.536
<i>♪ To laugh like a brook ♪</i>

1070
01:15:40.619 --> 01:15:42.496
-(humming)
<i>-♪ When it trips and falls ♪</i>

1071
01:15:42.579 --> 01:15:45.415
<i>♪ Over stones on its way ♪</i>

1072
01:15:45.499 --> 01:15:47.626
<i>♪ On its way ♪</i>

1073
01:15:47.709 --> 01:15:51.922
-(singing along)
<i>-♪ To sing through the night ♪</i>

1074
01:15:52.005 --> 01:15:57.803
<i>♪ Like a lark who is learning to pray ♪</i>

1075
01:15:57.886 --> 01:16:02.599
<i>♪ I go to the hills ♪</i>

1076
01:16:02.683 --> 01:16:07.896
<i>-♪ When my heart is lonely ♪</i>
-(children stop singing)

1077
01:16:08.981 --> 01:16:12.609
<i>♪ I know I will hear ♪</i>

1078
01:16:12.693 --> 01:16:19.032
<i>♪ What I've heard before ♪</i>

1079
01:16:19.116 --> 01:16:24.079
<i>-♪ My heart will be blessed ♪</i>
-(children harmonizing)

1080
01:16:24.162 --> 01:16:28.834
<i>♪ With the sound of music ♪</i>

1081
01:16:32.045 --> 01:16:34.339
<i>♪ And I'll ♪</i>

1082
01:16:34.423 --> 01:16:37.134
(with children) ♪<i> Sing </i>♪

1083
01:16:37.217 --> 01:16:40.345
<i>♪ Once ♪</i>

1084
01:16:40.429 --> 01:16:45.851
<i>♪ More ♪</i>

1085
01:17:02.951 --> 01:17:05.454
VON TRAPP (chuckles): Oh.

1086
01:17:18.675 --> 01:17:20.719
Edelweiss.

1087
01:17:24.598 --> 01:17:27.309
You never told me
how enchanting your children are.

1088
01:17:36.026 --> 01:17:37.778
Don't go away.

1089
01:17:42.783 --> 01:17:44.576
Fräulein.

1090
01:17:47.704 --> 01:17:48.997
I...

1091
01:17:50.374 --> 01:17:52.167
...behaved badly.

1092
01:17:52.250 --> 01:17:53.460
I apologize.

1093
01:17:55.087 --> 01:17:57.923
Oh, I'm far too outspoken.
It's one of my worst faults.

1094
01:17:58.965 --> 01:18:00.634
You were right.

1095
01:18:02.969 --> 01:18:04.513
I don't know my children.

1096
01:18:06.056 --> 01:18:09.476
There's still time, Captain.
They want so much to be close to you.

1097
01:18:10.769 --> 01:18:14.022
You brought music back into the house.

1098
01:18:15.440 --> 01:18:16.775
I'd forgotten.

1099
01:18:19.653 --> 01:18:21.196
Fräulein.

1100
01:18:23.490 --> 01:18:24.741
I want you to stay.

1101
01:18:29.287 --> 01:18:32.040
I... ask you to stay.

1102
01:18:33.208 --> 01:18:35.127
If I could be of any help--

1103
01:18:35.210 --> 01:18:38.755
You have already.
More than you know.

1104
01:18:58.400 --> 01:19:01.820
MARIA: Marta. Curtain!

1105
01:19:04.322 --> 01:19:06.992
MARIA:<i> ♪ High on a hill</i>
<i>was a lonely goatherd ♪</i>

1106
01:19:07.075 --> 01:19:09.286
<i>♪ Layee-o-dl layee-o-dl lay-ee-o ♪</i>

1107
01:19:09.369 --> 01:19:11.705
<i>♪ Loud was the voice</i>
<i>of the lonely goatherd ♪</i>

1108
01:19:11.788 --> 01:19:13.999
<i>♪ Layee-o-dl layee-o-dl-oo ♪</i>

1109
01:19:14.082 --> 01:19:16.460
<i>♪ Folks in a town that</i>
<i>was quite remote heard ♪</i>

1110
01:19:16.543 --> 01:19:18.795
<i>♪ Layee-o-dl layee-o-dl lay-ee-o ♪</i>

1111
01:19:18.879 --> 01:19:21.548
<i>♪ Lusty and clear</i>
<i>from the goatherd's throat heard ♪</i>

1112
01:19:21.631 --> 01:19:23.633
<i>♪ Layee-o-dl layee-o-dl-oo ♪</i>

1113
01:19:23.717 --> 01:19:26.178
CHILDREN:<i> ♪ O-ho laydee-o-dl-ee-o ♪</i>

1114
01:19:26.261 --> 01:19:28.346
<i>♪ O-ho laydee-o-dl-ay ♪</i>

1115
01:19:28.430 --> 01:19:30.766
<i>♪ O-ho laydee-o-dl-ee-o ♪</i>

1116
01:19:30.849 --> 01:19:33.185
<i>♪ Laydee-o-dl-ee o-lay ♪</i>

1117
01:19:33.268 --> 01:19:35.937
MARIA: Marta! Marta!

1118
01:19:36.021 --> 01:19:37.481
(gasps)

1119
01:19:38.732 --> 01:19:40.192
Gretl, the prince!

1120
01:19:42.527 --> 01:19:45.363
MARIA:<i> ♪ A prince on the bridge</i>
<i>of a castle moat heard ♪</i>

1121
01:19:45.447 --> 01:19:47.532
<i>♪ Layee-o-dl layee-o-dl lay-ee-oo ♪</i>

1122
01:19:47.616 --> 01:19:49.993
CHILDREN:<i> ♪ Men on a road</i>
<i>with a load to tote heard ♪</i>

1123
01:19:50.076 --> 01:19:52.537
<i>♪ Layee-o-dl layee o-dl-oo ♪</i>

1124
01:19:52.621 --> 01:19:54.706
<i>♪ Men in the midst</i>
<i>of a table d'hôte heard ♪</i>

1125
01:19:54.790 --> 01:19:57.292
<i>♪ Layee-o-dl layee-o-dl lay-ee-o ♪</i>

1126
01:19:57.375 --> 01:19:59.419
<i>♪ Men drinking beer</i>
<i>with the foam afloat heard ♪</i>

1127
01:19:59.503 --> 01:20:02.047
<i>♪ Layee-o-dl layee-o-dl-oo ♪</i>
(coughs)

1128
01:20:11.556 --> 01:20:13.725
MARIA:<i> ♪ One little girl</i>
<i>in a pale pink coat heard ♪</i>

1129
01:20:13.809 --> 01:20:16.186
<i>♪ Layee-o-dl</i>
<i>layee-o-dl lay-ee-o ♪</i>

1130
01:20:16.269 --> 01:20:18.563
<i>♪ She yodeled back</i>
<i>to the lonely goatherd ♪</i>

1131
01:20:18.647 --> 01:20:20.774
<i>♪ Layee-o-dl layee-o-dl-oo ♪</i>

1132
