-Yes?
-No.

1344
01:34:54.897 --> 01:34:56.691
(laughing)

1345
01:34:59.527 --> 01:35:01.654
<i>♪ So long, farewell ♪</i>

1346
01:35:01.737 --> 01:35:03.739
<i>♪ Auf Wiedersehen, goodbye ♪</i>

1347
01:35:03.823 --> 01:35:07.743
<i>♪ I leave and heave a sigh</i>
<i>and say goodbye ♪</i>

1348
01:35:07.827 --> 01:35:11.831
<i>♪ Goodbye ♪</i>

1349
01:35:14.792 --> 01:35:17.962
<i>♪ I'm glad to go ♪</i>

1350
01:35:18.045 --> 01:35:21.006
<i>♪ I cannot tell a lie ♪</i>

1351
01:35:21.090 --> 01:35:24.719
<i>♪ I flit, I float ♪</i>

1352
01:35:24.802 --> 01:35:27.805
<i>♪ I fleetly flee, I fly ♪</i>

1353
01:35:38.023 --> 01:35:40.151
<i>♪ The sun ♪</i>

1354
01:35:40.234 --> 01:35:43.904
<i>♪ Has gone to bed ♪</i>

1355
01:35:43.988 --> 01:35:47.908
<i>♪ And so must I ♪</i>

1356
01:35:47.992 --> 01:35:50.745
<i>♪ So long ♪</i>

1357
01:35:50.828 --> 01:35:53.664
<i>♪ Farewell ♪</i>

1358
01:35:53.748 --> 01:35:56.250
<i>♪ Auf Wiedersehen ♪</i>

1359
01:35:56.333 --> 01:35:59.170
<i>♪ Goodbye ♪</i>

1360
01:35:59.253 --> 01:36:04.425
<i>♪ Goodbye ♪</i>

1361
01:36:04.508 --> 01:36:10.806
<i>♪ Goodbye ♪</i>

1362
01:36:10.890 --> 01:36:15.603
<i>♪ Goodbye ♪</i>

1363
01:36:17.980 --> 01:36:22.026
<i>♪ Goodbye ♪</i>

1364
01:36:26.572 --> 01:36:31.202
(chatter resumes)

1365
01:36:31.285 --> 01:36:34.580
They're extraordinary.
What they would do at the festival!

1366
01:36:34.663 --> 01:36:36.332
Oh, young lady, I must
have words with you.

1367
01:36:36.415 --> 01:36:37.875
Congratulations.

1368
01:36:37.958 --> 01:36:40.795
Georg? Georg, you're not going
to let this girl get away.

1369
01:36:40.878 --> 01:36:42.254
She has to join the party.

1370
01:36:42.338 --> 01:36:44.965
-No, really, I--
-Shh. Stop. Stop it.

1371
01:36:45.049 --> 01:36:47.968
-Georg, please.
-You can if you want to, fräulein.

1372
01:36:48.052 --> 01:36:51.514
I insist. You will be my dinner partner.
This is business.

1373
01:36:51.597 --> 01:36:55.601
Franz, set another place
next to mine for Fräulein Maria.

1374
01:36:56.977 --> 01:36:59.063
Why-- Whatever you say,
Herr Detweiler.

1375
01:36:59.146 --> 01:37:01.148
It appears to be all arranged,
doesn't it?

1376
01:37:01.232 --> 01:37:03.776
-It certainly does.
-I'm not suitably dressed.

1377
01:37:03.859 --> 01:37:06.445
Uh, well, you can change.
We'll wait for you.

1378
01:37:07.905 --> 01:37:09.532
All right.

1379
01:37:09.615 --> 01:37:12.785
Captain, you must be very proud
of your youngsters.

1380
01:37:12.868 --> 01:37:14.245
I am. Thank you, Baroness.

1381
01:37:14.328 --> 01:37:18.332
Is there a more beautiful expression
of what is good in this country of ours...

1382
01:37:19.375 --> 01:37:22.002
...than the innocent voices
of our children?

1383
01:37:22.878 --> 01:37:24.964
Oh, come, now, Baron,
would you have us believe

1384
01:37:25.047 --> 01:37:28.259
that Austria alone holds
a monopoly on virtue?

1385
01:37:28.342 --> 01:37:33.347
Herr Zeller, some of us prefer
Austrian voices raised in song

1386
01:37:33.430 --> 01:37:35.891
to ugly German threats.

1387
01:37:36.934 --> 01:37:40.437
The, uh, ostrich buries his head
in the sand...

1388
01:37:40.521 --> 01:37:43.732
and sometimes... in the flag.

1389
01:37:43.816 --> 01:37:46.610
Perhaps those who would warn you
that the Anschluss is coming--

1390
01:37:46.694 --> 01:37:50.030
and it is coming, Captain--
perhaps they would get further with you

1391
01:37:50.114 --> 01:37:52.408
by setting their words to music.

1392
01:37:52.491 --> 01:37:54.410
If the Nazis take over Austria,

1393
01:37:54.493 --> 01:37:57.246
I have no doubt, Herr Zeller, that you
will be the entire trumpet section.

1394
01:37:57.329 --> 01:38:01.166
-You flatter me, Captain.
-Oh, how clumsy of me.

1395
01:38:01.250 --> 01:38:03.210
I meant to accuse you.

1396
01:38:11.051 --> 01:38:13.888
It's very kind of you
to offer to help me, Baroness.

1397
01:38:13.971 --> 01:38:15.931
I'm delighted, Maria.

1398
01:38:16.015 --> 01:38:19.059
I-- I really don't think I do have
anything that would be appropriate.

1399
01:38:20.144 --> 01:38:22.313
Now, where is that lovely little thing

1400
01:38:22.396 --> 01:38:24.565
you were wearing the other evening,

1401
01:38:24.648 --> 01:38:27.234
when the captain couldn't
keep his eyes off you?

1402
01:38:31.196 --> 01:38:32.781
Couldn't keep his eyes off me?

1403
01:38:34.116 --> 01:38:36.493
Come, my dear, we are women.

1404
01:38:36.577 --> 01:38:39.580
Let's not pretend we don't know
when a man notices us.

1405
01:38:39.663 --> 01:38:41.040
Here we are.

1406
01:38:41.123 --> 01:38:42.833
The captain notices
everybody and everything.

1407
01:38:43.709 --> 01:38:46.670
There's no need to feel
so defensive, Maria.

1408
01:38:46.754 --> 01:38:49.423
You are quite attractive, you know.

1409
01:38:49.506 --> 01:38:52.343
The captain would hardly be a man
if he didn't notice you.

1410
01:38:54.720 --> 01:38:57.264
Baroness, I hope you're joking.

1411
01:38:57.348 --> 01:39:00.351
-Not at all.
-But I've never done a thing to--

1412
01:39:00.434 --> 01:39:02.603
But you don't have to, my dear.

1413
01:39:02.686 --> 01:39:06.941
There's nothing more irresistible to a man
than a woman who's in love with him.

1414
01:39:09.026 --> 01:39:11.153
-In love with him?
-Of course.

1415
01:39:11.862 --> 01:39:16.158
But what makes it so nice
is he thinks he's in love with you.

1416
01:39:18.619 --> 01:39:20.412
But that's not true.

1417
01:39:20.496 --> 01:39:24.041
Surely you've noticed the way
he looks into your eyes.

1418
01:39:24.124 --> 01:39:26.961
And, you know, uh,
you blushed in his arms

1419
01:39:27.044 --> 01:39:28.963
when you were dancing just now.

1420
01:39:30.631 --> 01:39:31.715
Don't take it to heart.

1421
01:39:32.633 --> 01:39:34.843
He'll get over it soon enough,
I should think.

1422
01:39:34.927 --> 01:39:36.220
Men do, you know.

1423
01:39:38.055 --> 01:39:39.390
Then I should go.

1424
01:39:40.557 --> 01:39:42.226
I mustn't stay here.

1425
01:39:52.403 --> 01:39:55.614
-Is there something I can do to help?
-No, nothing.

1426
01:39:57.658 --> 01:40:02.121
Yes. Please don't say a word
about this to the captain.

1427
01:40:03.497 --> 01:40:06.458
No. No, I wouldn't dream of it.

1428
01:40:13.424 --> 01:40:15.634
Goodbye, Maria.

1429
01:40:15.718 --> 01:40:18.637
I'm sure you'll make a very fine nun.

1430
01:40:49.126 --> 01:40:51.462
Champagne, darling.

1431
01:40:51.545 --> 01:40:53.756
I feel like celebrating.

1432
01:40:53.839 --> 01:40:55.966
Cheers.

1433
01:41:00.971 --> 01:41:04.016
-You know something.
-Perhaps.

1434
01:41:04.099 --> 01:41:06.727
Then if you're so clever,
tell me how to get our little fräulein

1435
01:41:06.810 --> 01:41:09.021
to use her influence with Georg.

1436
01:41:09.104 --> 01:41:11.023
I want those children in the festival.

1437
01:41:12.274 --> 01:41:14.193
Elsa, this is important to Austria.

1438
01:41:14.276 --> 01:41:16.153
It wouldn't do you any harm either.

1439
01:41:16.236 --> 01:41:18.072
I've thought of that.

1440
01:41:18.155 --> 01:41:20.991
Well, if it's a matter of influence,

1441
01:41:21.075 --> 01:41:23.452
maybe the one you'll have
to be talking to is me.

1442
01:41:23.535 --> 01:41:25.621
(applause)

1443
01:42:44.575 --> 01:42:48.996
<i>(orchestra playing fanfare)</i>

1444
01:44:49.408 --> 01:44:51.326
-KURT: Two.
-MARTA: Three.

1445
01:44:51.410 --> 01:44:53.287
LIESL: Four.

1446
01:44:53.370 --> 01:44:56.206
-Five.
-BARONESS: Six.

1447
01:44:56.290 --> 01:44:59.251
-Seven.
-Eight.

1448
01:44:59.334 --> 01:45:00.794
-(baroness grunts)
-Four.

1449
01:45:00.877 --> 01:45:02.963
-LIESL: Two.
-KURT: Seven.

1450
01:45:03.046 --> 01:45:05.215
-BRIGITTA: Five.
-FRIEDRICH: Two!

1451
01:45:05.299 --> 01:45:07.259
-KURT: Six.
-Oh!

1452
01:45:07.342 --> 01:45:08.677
(chuckles)

1453
01:45:09.303 --> 01:45:10.804
(chuckles)

1454
01:45:10.887 --> 01:45:12.431
BARONESS: Isn't this fun?

1455
01:45:13.348 --> 01:45:14.683
Um...

1456
01:45:14.766 --> 01:45:16.685
-Four.
-I'm number five.

1457
01:45:16.768 --> 01:45:19.688
-Oh, yes.
-LIESL: Eight.

1458
01:45:19.771 --> 01:45:22.441
-LOUISA: Two.
-KURT: Four.

1459
01:45:22.524 --> 01:45:24.109
-Six!
-Ohh!

1460
01:45:24.192 --> 01:45:27.904
(groans) Two.

1461
01:45:27.988 --> 01:45:30.907
KURT: Baroness Schraeder,
do you mind if we stop now?

1462
01:45:30.991 --> 01:45:33.577
-We're tired.
-Oh, whatever you want, dear.

1463
01:45:33.660 --> 01:45:35.579
We'll do it again tomorrow.

1464
01:45:46.256 --> 01:45:48.717
The country's so restful, isn't it?

1465
01:45:48.800 --> 01:45:50.761
Have some lemonade.

1466
01:45:50.844 --> 01:45:54.139
Oh. There must be an easier way.

1467
01:45:55.474 --> 01:45:58.727
I get a fiendish delight thinking of you
as the mother of seven.

1468
01:45:58.810 --> 01:46:01.688
-Mm-hm.
-How do you plan to do it?

1469
01:46:01.772 --> 01:46:03.774
Darling, haven't you ever heard

1470
01:46:03.857 --> 01:46:07.152
of a delightful little thing
called boarding school?

1471
01:46:08.278 --> 01:46:10.947
-Baroness Machiavelli.
-Mm-hm.

1472
01:46:11.865 --> 01:46:15.285
-Uncle Max, where's Father?
-I think he's in the house.

1473
01:46:16.119 --> 01:46:18.163
What's the matter
with all you gloomy pusses?

1474
01:46:18.246 --> 01:46:20.874
-Nothing.
-I know what we'll do.

1475
01:46:20.957 --> 01:46:23.043
-Let's have a rehearsal.
-What for?

1476
01:46:23.126 --> 01:46:25.587
Let's make believe we're
standing on the stage at the festival.

1477
01:46:25.670 --> 01:46:27.506
I don't feel like singing.

1478
01:46:27.589 --> 01:46:29.800
Not without Fräulein Maria.

1479
01:46:29.883 --> 01:46:31.385
Liesl, get the guitar.
Come on, Marta.

1480
01:46:31.468 --> 01:46:33.178
-(children protesting)
-Everybody into the group.

1481
01:46:33.261 --> 01:46:35.097
You know your places in the group.
Get in your places.

1482
01:46:35.180 --> 01:46:37.933
That's right. Now, be cheerful.
Right, give us the key, Liesl.

1483
01:46:38.016 --> 01:46:40.268
(strumming guitar)

1484
01:46:40.352 --> 01:46:42.604
Now, impress me.

1485
01:46:42.687 --> 01:46:46.608
<i>-♪ Ah ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Ah ♪</i>

1486
01:46:46.691 --> 01:46:48.402
Friedrich, Gretl, why don't you sing?

1487
01:46:48.485 --> 01:46:51.822
I can't. I've got a sore finger.

1488
01:46:51.905 --> 01:46:55.242
But you sang so beautifully
the night of the party.

1489
01:46:55.325 --> 01:46:58.120
Come on, all of you. Sing something--
Try-- Try something you know.

1490
01:46:58.203 --> 01:47:00.747
Enjoy it. Be cheerful.
All right, Liesl.

1491
01:47:03.041 --> 01:47:08.171
<i>♪ The hills are alive ♪</i>

1492
01:47:08.255 --> 01:47:13.468
<i>♪ With the sound of music ♪</i>

1493
01:47:13.552 --> 01:47:17.347
LIESL:<i> ♪ Ah ah ah ah ♪</i>

1494
01:47:17.431 --> 01:47:22.686
<i>♪ With songs they have sung ♪</i>

1495
01:47:22.769 --> 01:47:27.399
<i>♪ For a thousand years ♪</i>

1496
01:47:27.482 --> 01:47:31.445
LIESL:<i> ♪ Ah ah ah ah ♪</i>

1497
01:47:31.528 --> 01:47:34.990
<i>♪ The hills fill my heart ♪</i>

1498
01:47:35.073 --> 01:47:37.075
<i>♪ Ah ah ah ah ♪</i>

1499
01:47:37.159 --> 01:47:41.288
<i>♪ With the sound of music ♪</i>

1500
01:47:41.371 --> 01:47:45.417
LIESL:<i> ♪ Ah ah ah ah ♪</i>

1501
01:47:45.500 --> 01:47:47.919
They, uh, just wanted to sing for me,
bless their hearts.

1502
01:47:48.003 --> 01:47:51.840
That's lovely, lovely.
Don't stop. Hmm?

1503
01:47:53.383 --> 01:47:56.261
-(Georg whistling)
-Uh, something long and cool, Georg?

1504
01:47:56.344 --> 01:47:58.346
No, thank you, darling.

1505
01:47:58.430 --> 01:48:00.974
-Father?
-Yes, Brigitta?

1506
01:48:01.057 --> 01:48:03.727
Is it true Fräulein Maria
isn't coming back?

1507
01:48:03.810 --> 01:48:05.812
Fräulein Maria?
Yes, I suppose it's true, yes.

1508
01:48:05.896 --> 01:48:08.732
-What have we got here?
-BARONESS: Pink lemonade.

1509
01:48:08.815 --> 01:48:12.360
-Laced with, uh, lemonade.
-Ooh.

1510
01:48:12.444 --> 01:48:14.321
I don't believe it, Father.

1511
01:48:14.404 --> 01:48:16.406
Hmm? Don't believe what, darling?

1512
01:48:16.490 --> 01:48:19.201
-About Fräulein Maria.
-Oh, Fräulein Maria!

1513
01:48:19.284 --> 01:48:22.454
Didn't I tell you what her note said?
Oh, I'm sure I did.

1514
01:48:23.747 --> 01:48:26.500
She said she missed her life
at the abbey too much.

1515
01:48:26.583 --> 01:48:28.168
She had to leave us.

1516
01:48:28.919 --> 01:48:30.545
And that's all there is to it.

1517
01:48:32.339 --> 01:48:34.424
I think I'm brave enough
to try some of that.

1518
01:48:35.175 --> 01:48:36.843
She didn't even say goodbye.

1519
01:48:36.927 --> 01:48:39.888
-She did in her note.
-LOUISA: That isn't the same thing.

1520
01:48:39.971 --> 01:48:42.057
Not too sweet, not too sour.

1521
01:48:42.140 --> 01:48:45.894
-Just too, uh... (clears throat) pink.
-(chuckles)

1522
01:48:45.977 --> 01:48:47.145
-GRETL: Father.
-Hmm?

1523
01:48:47.229 --> 01:48:49.439
Who is our new governess going to be?

1524
01:48:55.737 --> 01:48:57.072
Well...

1525
01:48:59.407 --> 01:49:04.621
You're not going to have
a governess anymore.

1526
01:49:04.704 --> 01:49:06.748
-CHILDREN: We're not?
-No.

1527
01:49:08.917 --> 01:49:10.835
You're going to have a new mother.

1528
01:49:12.754 --> 01:49:14.506
A new mother?

1529
01:49:15.757 --> 01:49:18.218
We talked about it last night.
It's all settled.

1530
01:49:19.177 --> 01:49:20.971
And we're all going to be very happy.

1531
01:49:21.054 --> 01:49:22.681
Hmm?

1532
01:49:54.379 --> 01:49:57.215
Well, all right, all right, all right.
Now, run off and play.

1533
01:50:21.072 --> 01:50:23.033
(doorbell rings)

1534
01:50:29.080 --> 01:50:30.624
Yes, my children?

1535
01:50:30.707 --> 01:50:32.959
-Uh, my name is Liesl.
-Yes, Liesl?

1536
01:50:33.043 --> 01:50:37.547
We-- my brothers and sisters--
we want to see Fräulein Maria.

1537
01:50:38.673 --> 01:50:40.342
Fräulein Maria?

1538
01:50:41.134 --> 01:50:42.927
Oh, Maria!

1539
01:50:44.721 --> 01:50:46.556
Come in, please.

1540
01:50:50.894 --> 01:50:52.729
Wait here.

1541
01:51:03.281 --> 01:51:06.618
I'm Sister Margaretta. I understand
you've been inquiring about Maria.

1542
01:51:06.701 --> 01:51:09.371
-We have to see her.
-Will you tell her we're here, please?

1543
01:51:09.454 --> 01:51:11.831
-I'm afraid I can't do that.
-Oh, but you've got to.

1544
01:51:11.915 --> 01:51:13.541
-We have to see her.
-She's our governess.

1545
01:51:13.625 --> 01:51:16.544
-We want her back!
-KURT: She didn't even say goodbye.

1546
01:51:16.628 --> 01:51:18.672
-It's very important.
-All we want to do is talk to her.

1547
01:51:19.422 --> 01:51:22.425
I'm very sorry, children,
but Maria is in seclusion.

1548
01:51:22.509 --> 01:51:23.802
She hasn't been seeing anyone.

1549
01:51:23.885 --> 01:51:25.720
She'll see us. I know she will.

1550
01:51:25.804 --> 01:51:28.473
I want to show her my finger.

1551
01:51:28.556 --> 01:51:30.517
Oh, some other time, dear.

1552
01:51:30.600 --> 01:51:33.144
I'll tell her that you were here.
It was sweet of you to call.

1553
01:51:33.228 --> 01:51:35.480
-BRIGITTA: Oh, we have to speak to her!
-MARTA: Please!

1554
01:51:35.563 --> 01:51:38.650
-(children clamoring)
-Run along, children. Run along home.

1555
01:51:41.528 --> 01:51:43.988
-Sister Margaretta!
-Please! Please!

1556
01:51:44.072 --> 01:51:46.866
-Goodbye, children.
-Please. Please.

1557
01:51:50.078 --> 01:51:52.122
What was that about,
Sister Margaretta?

1558
01:51:52.205 --> 01:51:56.418
The von Trapp children, Reverend Mother.
They want to see Maria.

1559
01:51:57.502 --> 01:52:00.046
Has she spoken yet?
Has she told you anything?

1560
01:52:00.130 --> 01:52:03.591
She doesn't say a word, Reverend Mother,
except in prayer.

1561
01:52:03.675 --> 01:52:05.510
Poor child.

1562
01:52:05.593 --> 01:52:08.638
It's strange.
She seems happy to be back here,

1563
01:52:08.722 --> 01:52:11.599
and yet-- and yet she's unhappy too.

1564
01:52:13.017 --> 01:52:16.354
Perhaps I have been wrong
in leaving her alone so long.

1565
01:52:16.438 --> 01:52:19.190
I think you'd better bring her to me,
even if she's not yet ready.

1566
01:52:19.274 --> 01:52:21.401
Yes, Reverend Mother.

1567
01:52:26.740 --> 01:52:30.160
Sister Augusta, take our
new postulant to the robing room.

1568
01:52:30.243 --> 01:52:32.746
God bless you, my daughter.

1569
01:52:32.829 --> 01:52:34.914
-(knocking)
-Ave!

1570
01:52:39.127 --> 01:52:40.920
Yes, bring her in.

1571
01:52:50.221 --> 01:52:52.724
You've been unhappy.
I'm sorry.

1572
01:52:53.892 --> 01:52:55.894
Reverend Mother.

1573
01:52:55.977 --> 01:52:59.022
Why did they send you back to us?

1574
01:52:59.105 --> 01:53:01.775
They didn't send me back,
Mother. I left.

1575
01:53:03.860 --> 01:53:06.863
Sit down, Maria.
Tell me what happened.

1576
01:53:10.700 --> 01:53:14.537
Well, I-- I was frightened.

1577
01:53:14.621 --> 01:53:17.832
Frightened?
Were they unkind to you?

1578
01:53:17.916 --> 01:53:21.503
Oh, no. No, I was--
I was confused.

1579
01:53:21.586 --> 01:53:22.796
I-- I felt--

1580
01:53:24.506 --> 01:53:27.759
I've never felt that way before.
I couldn't stay.

1581
01:53:27.842 --> 01:53:31.012
I knew that here I'd be away from it.
I'd be... safe.

1582
01:53:31.095 --> 01:53:35.141
Maria, our abbey
is not to be used as an escape.

1583
01:53:36.059 --> 01:53:37.268
What is it you can't face?

1584
01:53:40.271 --> 01:53:43.358
-I can't face him again.
-Him?

1585
01:53:45.652 --> 01:53:47.320
Thank you, Sister Margaretta.

1586
01:53:57.205 --> 01:53:59.082
Captain von Trapp?

1587
01:54:04.504 --> 01:54:06.881
-Are you in love with him?
-I don't know!

1588
01:54:06.965 --> 01:54:10.635
I don't know, I--
The baroness said I was.

1589
01:54:10.718 --> 01:54:13.471
She-- She said that
he was in love with me,

1590
01:54:13.555 --> 01:54:15.765
but I-- I didn't want to believe it.

1591
01:54:16.933 --> 01:54:19.102
Oh, there were times when
we would look at each other,

1592
01:54:19.185 --> 01:54:21.229
oh, Mother, I could hardly breathe.

1593
01:54:21.312 --> 01:54:23.022
Did you let him see how you felt?

1594
01:54:23.106 --> 01:54:25.900
If I did, I didn't know it.
That's what's been torturing me.

1595
01:54:25.984 --> 01:54:27.610
I was there on God's errand.

1596
01:54:27.694 --> 01:54:29.571
To have asked for his love
would have been wrong.

1597
01:54:29.654 --> 01:54:31.990
I couldn't stay. I just couldn't!

1598
01:54:34.868 --> 01:54:37.829
I'm ready at this moment
to take my vows.

1599
01:54:37.912 --> 01:54:39.914
Please help me.

1600
01:54:39.998 --> 01:54:45.795
Maria, the love of a man
and a woman is holy, too.

1601
01:54:45.879 --> 01:54:48.047
You have a great capacity to love.

1602
01:54:48.131 --> 01:54:51.342
What you must find out is how God
wants you to spend your love.

1603
01:54:51.426 --> 01:54:55.346
But I've pledged my life to God. I--
I've pledged my life to His service.

1604
01:54:55.430 --> 01:54:58.933
My daughter, if you love this man,
it doesn't mean you love God less.

1605
01:55:01.019 --> 01:55:05.148
No. You must find out.

1606
01:55:07.191 --> 01:55:08.610
You must go back.

1607
01:55:09.819 --> 01:55:11.696
Oh, Mother, you can't ask me to do that.

1608
01:55:11.779 --> 01:55:13.489
Please let me stay. I beg of you.

1609
01:55:13.573 --> 01:55:18.661
Maria, these walls were not built
to shut out problems.

1610
01:55:18.745 --> 01:55:20.580
You have to face them.

1611
01:55:20.663 --> 01:55:23.750
You have to live the life
you were born to live.

1612
01:55:30.423 --> 01:55:34.177
<i>♪ Climb every mountain ♪</i>

1613
01:55:34.260 --> 01:55:38.473
<i>♪ Search high and low ♪</i>

1614
